<TITLE> Abu Alam becomes DS, finally </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Mar 24 (bdnews24.com)-- Abu Alam Shahid Khan, a 1982 'regular batch' BCS officer, has finally been promoted to deputy secretary. Khan's all other batch-mates are now additional secretaries. A deputy press secretary at the PMO during the 1996-2001 Sheikh Hasina government, Khan languished for long as senior assistant secretary and had been overlooked for promotion for more than seven years because of his alleged proximity to the Awami League. He was made an OSD at establishment, pending assignment. Another senior assistant secretary, Mikail Shipar, was promoted. Shipar is now posted as a director at the 
